divs: Sighting DetailsWhile looking for my boomerang in some tall grass I found what I initially believed to be an egg. It was about the size of a chicken's egg but was sort of squishy. It was mostly white with a light grey mottled color and had a small, shriveled umbilical about one inch long. I took it to the house and set up a cement block and brought out my dissecting kit. With a scalpal I cut into it to reveal a skin about one mm thick or a little less revealing what looked like fish flesh. You could see an extremely fine tracery of capillaries and it exuded a small amount of a somewhat sticky and clear fluid. Cutting through that revealed a central 'core' of a brilliant orange, three fingered arrangement that clasped a blue sphere. The orange and blue portions were crennelated much as brain matter it and also showed a very fine tracery of capillaried. My mom called me into the house for lunch and upon returning to the front yard I discovered about 10 or 12 cats eating everything but the 'core'! Very disappointed (as I knew my neighbors were both biologists at the local University) I decided to plant the core in a small pot of soil and put it inside the house. About seven days later I realized that that move did not make any sense and took the pot outside and with a spoon carefully scraped the soil out. There was nothing to be found, not even a wet spot. I've been wanting to re-create this object with the appropriately colored clays for years and can do so, just haven't done so yet.
